This paper investigates the properties of the ImageNet dataset that are critical for learning good, general-purpose features for transfer learning. The paper focuses on pre-training CNN features on various subsets of the ImageNet dataset and evaluating transfer performance on various tasks. This work is highly relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) as it explores the effectiveness of pre-training on a large-scale image dataset for transfer learning. Additionally, the paper involves empirical investigation and evaluation of transfer performance, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and multimedia (cs.MM).
